00:20:30,250 --> 00:20:32,458
Picard to Commander Riker.

354
00:20:32,458 --> 00:20:34,000
Answer, please.

355
00:20:36,542 --> 00:20:38,959
Computer,
locate Commander Riker.

356
00:20:38,959 --> 00:20:42,583
COMPUTER: Commander Riker
is in his quarters.

357
00:20:42,583 --> 00:20:44,625
On my way, sir.

358
00:21:01,208 --> 00:21:04,709
DR. CRUSHER:
<i>Medical Log, Stardate 45431.7.</i>

359
00:21:04,709 --> 00:21:06,792
<i>Commander Riker</i>
<i>is the second officer</i>

360
00:21:06,792 --> 00:21:09,250
<i>who has fallen into an</i>
<i>unexplained coma.</i>

361
00:21:09,250 --> 00:21:11,917
<i>I have examined the Ullians,</i>
<i>and ruled out the possibility</i>

362
00:21:11,917 --> 00:21:14,333
<i>that they carry</i>
<i>a harmful organism.</i>

363
00:21:14,333 --> 00:21:16,458
I compared Deanna's
brain scan to the one

364
00:21:16,458 --> 00:21:18,250
that I took during
her last physical.

365
00:21:18,250 --> 00:21:19,709
There is a difference.

366
00:21:19,709 --> 00:21:22,625
This time, there's a trace
of electropathic activity.

367
00:21:22,625 --> 00:21:24,041
And Commander Riker?

368
00:21:24,041 --> 00:21:26,250
I found the same pattern.
If I didn't know better,

369
00:21:26,250 --> 00:21:28,250
I'd say they both had
Iresine Syndrome.

370
00:21:28,250 --> 00:21:29,750
That's the only
medical condition

371
00:21:29,750 --> 00:21:31,625
that would produce
that pattern.

372
00:21:31,625 --> 00:21:33,083
What is Iresine Syndrome?

373
00:21:33,083 --> 00:21:35,083
A very rare
neurological disorder

374
00:21:35,083 --> 00:21:37,500
first diagnosed in
the 23rd century.

375
00:21:37,500 --> 00:21:41,041
It's characterized by an
identical electropathic residue.

376
00:21:41,041 --> 00:21:42,709
Why discount the possibility

377
00:21:42,709 --> 00:21:44,750
that it's responsible
for these comas?

378
00:21:44,750 --> 00:21:46,417
Iresine is always accompanied

379
00:21:46,417 --> 00:21:48,917
by a severely decreased
histamine count.

380
00:21:48,917 --> 00:21:51,417
Both Will and Deanna
showed normal levels.

381
00:21:51,417 --> 00:21:52,875
I've asked
Commander La Forge

382
00:21:52,875 --> 00:21:54,458
to conduct a shipwide
diagnostic

383
00:21:54,458 --> 00:21:56,625
to determine any other agent
that might cause

384
00:21:56,625 --> 00:21:58,583
the same
electropathic pattern.

385
00:21:58,583 --> 00:22:00,667
Commander Riker and
Counselor Troi

386
00:22:00,667 --> 00:22:04,125
were in perfect health
until the Ullians arrived.

387
00:22:04,125 --> 00:22:07,417
It would be wise to quarantine
the aliens.

388
00:22:07,417 --> 00:22:09,083
I believe that
it would be premature

389
00:22:09,083 --> 00:22:10,667
to take that action, Mr. Worf.

390
00:22:10,667 --> 00:22:13,583
There's no real evidence
linking these comas

391
00:22:13,583 --> 00:22:15,000
with the Ullians.

392
00:22:15,000 --> 00:22:16,875
That's true, but there
is something curious.

393
00:22:16,875 --> 00:22:19,041
The electropathic residue
I discovered

394
00:22:19,041 --> 00:22:21,000
is located in the thalamus.

395
00:22:21,000 --> 00:22:23,125
That's the area
of the cerebral cortex

396
00:22:23,125 --> 00:22:25,500
that involves memory function.

397
00:22:27,375 --> 00:22:29,417
I've been accused
of putting people to sleep

398
00:22:29,417 --> 00:22:31,959
with one too many
stories, Captain.

399
00:22:31,959 --> 00:22:34,125
But this is the first time
it's ever been suggested

400
00:22:34,125 --> 00:22:36,625
that I might be the
cause of someone's coma.

401
00:22:36,625 --> 00:22:39,000
I mean no disrespect,
but we are faced

402
00:22:39,000 --> 00:22:40,875
with an alarming situation.

403
00:22:40,875 --> 00:22:43,542
Why do you suspect us,
Captain?

404
00:22:43,542 --> 00:22:45,500
Suspect is perhaps
too strong a word.

405
00:22:45,500 --> 00:22:47,417
I'm simply trying to
determine what has caused

406
00:22:47,417 --> 00:22:49,542
two of my officers to
fall into comas.

407
00:22:49,542 --> 00:22:51,834
But you've already
examined us.

408
00:22:51,834 --> 00:22:53,500
We aren't carrying
anything harmful.

409
00:22:53,500 --> 00:22:55,583
BEVERLY: In further
study of the victims,

410
00:22:55,583 --> 00:22:57,375
I detected some
abnormal patterns

411
00:22:57,375 --> 00:22:59,458
in the area of the brain
that involves memory.

412
00:22:59,458 --> 00:23:02,625
In the light of your
telepathic abilities,

413
00:23:02,625 --> 00:23:04,083
it raises the question.

414
00:23:04,083 --> 00:23:07,709
Captain, it is not our
wish to obstruct you.

415
00:23:07,709 --> 00:23:09,291
What would you like?

416
00:23:09,291 --> 00:23:12,917
If I could do some further
examinations tomorrow--

417
00:23:12,917 --> 00:23:15,750
perhaps monitor you
during a memory probe.

418
00:23:15,750 --> 00:23:18,917
Scrutiny does not frighten us.

419
00:23:18,917 --> 00:23:21,583
We will be happy
to cooperate, Doctor.

420
00:23:22,792 --> 00:23:23,834
Thank you.

421
00:23:23,834 --> 00:23:26,333
I'll contact you
in the morning.

422
00:23:31,709 --> 00:23:33,250
Since you're
the only person on board

423
00:23:33,250 --> 00:23:35,500
to undergo a memory probe
by the Ullians,

424
00:23:35,500 --> 00:23:37,291
I'd like to do
a neurological work-up

425
00:23:37,291 --> 00:23:39,625
and see if I can detect
any residual effect.

426
00:23:39,625 --> 00:23:41,542
Dr. Martin will
monitor your vital signs

427
00:23:41,542 --> 00:23:42,834
while I conduct the scan.

428
00:23:42,834 --> 00:23:44,583
I'm happy to help.

429
00:23:46,000 --> 00:23:47,917
Have you noticed
any unusual symptoms

430
00:23:47,917 --> 00:23:49,458
since the probe?

431
00:23:49,458 --> 00:23:51,834
Headaches,
dizziness?

432
00:23:51,834 --> 00:23:53,125
No, nothing like that.

433
00:23:53,125 --> 00:23:55,542
It was a wonderful
experience.

434
00:23:56,959 --> 00:23:59,333
Electrical activity
is normal.

435
00:23:59,333 --> 00:24:01,333
C.P.K. levels are normal.

436
00:24:01,333 --> 00:24:05,625
Hippocampus is stable...
and the thalamus...

437
00:24:07,458 --> 00:24:09,333
The thalamus is normal.

438
00:24:09,333 --> 00:24:13,083
There is no indication at all
of any electropathic residual.

439
00:24:13,083 --> 00:24:14,834
Is that good?

440
00:24:14,834 --> 00:24:17,208
Oh, you're fine, Keiko.

441
00:24:17,208 --> 00:24:20,208
But I am no closer to
solving this mystery.

442
00:24:21,583 --> 00:24:24,333
Computer, locate
the electropathic pattern

443
00:24:24,333 --> 00:24:27,208
described in medical database
four-delta-one.

444
00:24:27,208 --> 00:24:29,583
COMPUTER:
Electropathic pattern located.

445
00:24:29,583 --> 00:24:32,208
Okay, we're going to track down

446
00:24:32,208 --> 00:24:35,250
any possible cause
of that brain pattern.

447
00:24:35,250 --> 00:24:37,166
First, what are the medical
conditions

448
00:24:37,166 --> 00:24:38,792
that might account for it?

449
00:24:38,792 --> 00:24:40,667
COMPUTER:
Iresine Syndrome is a cause

450
00:24:40,667 --> 00:24:42,875
of the electropathic pattern.

451
00:24:42,875 --> 00:24:45,375
Right, and Dr. Crusher
already eliminated that.

452
00:24:45,375 --> 00:24:49,083
So, how many non-medical
forces or substances

453
00:24:49,083 --> 00:24:50,709
might cause the pattern?

454
00:24:50,709 --> 00:24:53,333
COMPUTER:
There are 22 non-medical agents.

455
00:24:53,333 --> 00:24:57,166
Okay, and how many of those
are present on the<i> Enterprise?</i>

456
00:24:57,166 --> 00:25:00,166
COMPUTER: None are present
on the<i> Enterprise.</i>

457
00:25:00,166 --> 00:25:01,750
Are the ship's
sensors calibrated

458
00:25:01,750 --> 00:25:03,625
to detect all those agents?

459
00:25:03,625 --> 00:25:06,208
COMPUTER: All agents are
scanned by the sensors.

460
00:25:07,750 --> 00:25:12,500
Okay. Let's start
with the chemical substances.

461
00:25:12,500 --> 00:25:14,250
Name them.

462
00:25:14,250 --> 00:25:18,291
COMPUTER: Ferrazene,
hylanatine, dardilion,

463
00:25:18,291 --> 00:25:21,709
chrysimite, and manzene.

464
00:25:21,709 --> 00:25:23,125
Hmm.

465
00:25:23,125 --> 00:25:25,542
Ferrazene has a complex
molecular structure.

466
00:25:25,542 --> 00:25:29,166
It breaks down
into bilenium and tarrisite.

467
00:25:29,166 --> 00:25:30,959
Do the sensors scan for those?

468
00:25:30,959 --> 00:25:33,375
COMPUTER: Ship's sensors
scan for both compounds.

469
00:25:33,375 --> 00:25:35,417
And are they present
on the<i> Enterprise?</i>

470
00:25:35,417 --> 00:25:38,667
COMPUTER: Bilenium and
tarrisite are not present.

471
00:25:38,667 --> 00:25:41,667
Do any of the substances
break down into by-products

472
00:25:41,667 --> 00:25:43,417
that are not scanned for?

473
00:25:43,417 --> 00:25:46,333
COMPUTER: Dardilion contains
the by-product nilizene.

474
00:25:46,333 --> 00:25:49,792
Sensors do not routinely
scan for that substance.

475
00:25:49,792 --> 00:25:52,333
Well, this isn't
a routine situation.

476
00:25:52,333 --> 00:25:54,125
Scan for the nilizene.

477
00:25:54,125 --> 00:25:57,041
COMUTER: There is no nilizene
on the<i> Enterprise.</i>

478
00:25:57,041 --> 00:26:00,750
How did I know
you were gonna say that?

479
00:26:00,750 --> 00:26:05,583
Okay, let's move on to the
non-chemical agents.

480
00:26:10,458 --> 00:26:12,625
Anything more
I can do for you?

481
00:26:12,625 --> 00:26:14,208
No, thanks.

482
00:26:14,208 --> 00:26:16,875
I was just doing some reading
on the Iresine Syndrome.

483
00:26:16,875 --> 00:26:18,875
If a new strain has developed,
that might explain

484
00:26:18,875 --> 00:26:21,000
the normal histamine counts.

485
00:26:21,000 --> 00:26:22,542
Any luck?

486
00:26:22,542 --> 00:26:24,625
Not so far.

487
00:26:24,625 --> 00:26:27,166
Okay. I'll see you tomorrow.

488
00:26:37,333 --> 00:26:39,875
PICARD: You shouldn't
remember him like this.

489
00:26:43,792 --> 00:26:46,083
You don't have to do this.

490
00:26:46,083 --> 00:26:49,333
It's important to me.
I have to see him.

491
00:27:01,709 --> 00:27:03,792
It's good of you
to come.

492
00:27:03,792 --> 00:27:06,125
It's the least
I can do.

493
00:27:12,250 --> 00:27:15,750
PICARD: You shouldn't
remember him like this.

494
00:27:15,750 --> 00:27:18,125
BEVERLY: I have to face
the fact that he's gone.

495
00:27:27,792 --> 00:27:29,917
You shouldn't
remember him like this.

496
00:27:29,917 --> 00:27:31,792
It's good of you
to come with me.

497
00:27:31,792 --> 00:27:33,750
It's the least I can do.

498
00:27:38,834 --> 00:27:41,583
You shouldn't
remember him like this.

499
00:27:45,500 --> 00:27:47,709
(<i> Jev's voice:</i> )
It's the least I can do.

500
00:27:55,458 --> 00:27:57,041
(<i> gasps</i> )

501
00:28:01,333 --> 00:28:03,959
(<i> screaming</i> )

502
