I've spent two hours

503
00:28:07,417 --> 00:28:09,291
having a cozy little
chat with the computer.

504
00:28:09,291 --> 00:28:11,125
I've checked everything
I could think of--

505
00:28:11,125 --> 00:28:13,000
any possible agent
that might cause

506
00:28:13,000 --> 00:28:14,542
that electropathic pattern.

507
00:28:14,542 --> 00:28:17,041
I assume from your tone of
voice you were unsuccessful.

508
00:28:17,041 --> 00:28:18,750
Didn't find a thing.

509
00:28:20,083 --> 00:28:22,166
Dr. Crusher's not gonna
be too happy with...

510
00:28:24,041 --> 00:28:25,333
Emergency medical team

511
00:28:25,333 --> 00:28:27,792
to Dr. Crusher's
office immediately.

512
00:28:36,709 --> 00:28:40,041
Dr. Crusher had me working
on a shipwide diagnostic.

513
00:28:40,041 --> 00:28:42,041
I'd gone to give her
the results when I found her.

514
00:28:42,041 --> 00:28:44,792
Did your scans provide any
insights into these comas?

515
00:28:44,792 --> 00:28:46,792
None. I've checked
and cross-checked.

516
00:28:46,792 --> 00:28:48,208
They're just dead ends.

517
00:28:48,208 --> 00:28:50,583
We seem to have eliminated all
of the known factors

518
00:28:50,583 --> 00:28:52,250
which may have
caused the comas,

519
00:28:52,250 --> 00:28:54,166
except for the Ullians.

520
00:28:54,166 --> 00:28:56,709
Mr. Data, I want you
to investigate

521
00:28:56,709 --> 00:28:59,333
those 11 planets
that the Ullians visited.

522
00:28:59,333 --> 00:29:02,000
See if there were any reports
of unexplained comas.

523
00:29:02,000 --> 00:29:03,041
Aye, sir.

524
00:29:03,041 --> 00:29:06,542
In the meantime,
we must consider

525
00:29:06,542 --> 00:29:08,583
restricting them
to their quarters

526
00:29:08,583 --> 00:29:10,041
as a precautionary measure.

527
00:29:10,041 --> 00:29:11,458
If one of them
is behind this,

528
00:29:11,458 --> 00:29:13,208
will keeping telepaths
in their quarters

529
00:29:13,208 --> 00:29:14,834
prevent it from
happening again?

530
00:29:14,834 --> 00:29:16,750
What else can we do?

531
00:29:16,750 --> 00:29:19,291
Station a guard?
Set up a force field?

532
00:29:19,291 --> 00:29:21,417
I don't see that those will
be any more effective.

533
00:29:21,417 --> 00:29:23,000
DR. MARTIN:
Sick Bay to Captain Picard.

534
00:29:23,000 --> 00:29:24,500
Picard here.

535
00:29:24,500 --> 00:29:26,375
DR. MARTIN: Counselor Troi
has regained consciousness.

536
00:29:26,375 --> 00:29:28,709
She's asked for you, sir.

537
00:29:28,709 --> 00:29:30,417
I'm on my way.

538
00:29:32,208 --> 00:29:34,458
It's like waking up
from a nightmare,

539
00:29:34,458 --> 00:29:36,917
and not remembering
what it was about.

540
00:29:36,917 --> 00:29:39,458
What is the last thing
you do remember?

541
00:29:41,333 --> 00:29:44,792
My hair.
I was brushing my hair.

542
00:29:45,875 --> 00:29:47,041
And then?

543
00:29:48,917 --> 00:29:51,125
(<i> sighs</i> )
I don't know.

544
00:29:51,125 --> 00:29:53,083
Just waking up here.

545
00:29:54,834 --> 00:29:58,250
Why do I feel so frightened?
What happened to me?

546
00:30:02,208 --> 00:30:04,917
We were hoping
that you could tell us.

547
00:30:06,041 --> 00:30:07,417
How long have I been here?

548
00:30:07,417 --> 00:30:09,583
Three days.

549
00:30:09,583 --> 00:30:11,041
Three days?

550
00:30:11,041 --> 00:30:12,917
You were the first.

551
00:30:12,917 --> 00:30:17,375
The next day, Commander Riker
fell into a similar coma.

552
00:30:17,375 --> 00:30:19,709
Last night,
Dr. Crusher.

553
00:30:19,709 --> 00:30:21,834
What is going on here?

554
00:30:21,834 --> 00:30:23,792
We're not certain.

555
00:30:23,792 --> 00:30:26,834
It may be that there
is some unusual effect

556
00:30:26,834 --> 00:30:30,583
produced by the Ullians'
telepathic activity.

557
00:30:30,583 --> 00:30:32,625
I'm gonna talk to them.
And in the meantime,

558
00:30:32,625 --> 00:30:35,375
you are to stay here
and recuperate.

559
00:30:35,375 --> 00:30:38,625
But if you remember anything
at all about what happened,

560
00:30:38,625 --> 00:30:41,291
I want you to
tell me immediately.

561
00:30:51,625 --> 00:30:54,500
What are you suggesting,
Captain?

562
00:30:54,500 --> 00:30:57,625
That you voluntarily confine
yourself to your quarters,

563
00:30:57,625 --> 00:30:59,917
at least until we have
unravelled this mystery.

564
00:30:59,917 --> 00:31:01,250
We're to be prisoners?

565
00:31:01,250 --> 00:31:02,750
Father.

566
00:31:02,750 --> 00:31:05,542
PICARD: No, please,
don't look on it like that.

567
00:31:05,542 --> 00:31:08,583
We have done
everything we can

568
00:31:08,583 --> 00:31:10,500
to explain these comas.

569
00:31:10,500 --> 00:31:12,709
We have performed
physical examinations,

570
00:31:12,709 --> 00:31:14,083
neurological scans.

571
00:31:14,083 --> 00:31:16,959
We have conducted
a shipwide diagnostic

572
00:31:16,959 --> 00:31:21,250
looking for viruses,
parasites, infestations.

573
00:31:21,250 --> 00:31:23,792
We have investigated every
possible cause we could imagine,

574
00:31:23,792 --> 00:31:26,166
and we have found nothing--

575
00:31:26,166 --> 00:31:29,625
nothing to explain
these comas.

576
00:31:29,625 --> 00:31:34,333
The only variable that we have
not been able to eliminate

577
00:31:34,333 --> 00:31:37,500
is your presence
here on this ship.

578
00:31:37,500 --> 00:31:40,750
Now, in the light
of our actions,

579
00:31:40,750 --> 00:31:45,625
we would ask you to understand
my request and to agree to it.

580
00:31:49,583 --> 00:31:51,917
Captain, our history indicates

581
00:31:51,917 --> 00:31:55,083
that we do not adversely affect
the people we contact.

582
00:31:55,083 --> 00:31:57,083
I know that.

583
00:31:57,083 --> 00:32:00,917
Then... are you implying
an intentional assault?

584
00:32:00,917 --> 00:32:04,834
I'm simply considering
all possibilities.

585
00:32:04,834 --> 00:32:06,208
Surely, you would
give us the chance

586
00:32:06,208 --> 00:32:07,667
to prove that we're innocent?

587
00:32:07,667 --> 00:32:09,542
If that's possible,
of course.

588
00:32:09,542 --> 00:32:11,875
Well, then I would propose

589
00:32:11,875 --> 00:32:14,041
doing a memory probe
of Counselor Troi.

590
00:32:14,041 --> 00:32:16,041
You have said

591
00:32:16,041 --> 00:32:18,792
that she doesn't remember
anything that happened

592
00:32:18,792 --> 00:32:21,166
before she lapsed
into unconsciousness.

593
00:32:21,166 --> 00:32:23,583
I could retrieve that memory.

594
00:32:23,583 --> 00:32:27,208
There is a possibility that
it could explain the coma

595
00:32:27,208 --> 00:32:28,709
and prove our innocence.

596
00:32:30,291 --> 00:32:33,792
I'm sorry, I couldn't possibly
subject Counselor Troi

597
00:32:33,792 --> 00:32:37,041
to a potentially
dangerous procedure.

598
00:32:37,041 --> 00:32:40,083
And I refuse to be a party
to any of these proceedings.

599
00:32:42,333 --> 00:32:45,417
Jev is making a reasonable
request, Captain.

600
00:32:45,417 --> 00:32:46,959
If we're to be accused,

601
00:32:46,959 --> 00:32:49,834
surely, we're entitled
to a defense.

602
00:32:51,291 --> 00:32:53,667
Tarmin did a memory
probe on another

603
00:32:53,667 --> 00:32:54,875
of your crew.

604
00:32:54,875 --> 00:32:56,917
Has she suffered
any ill effects?

605
00:32:56,917 --> 00:32:58,166
No.

606
00:32:58,166 --> 00:33:00,667
And neither will
Counselor Troi.

607
00:33:00,667 --> 00:33:02,208
Please.

608
00:33:02,208 --> 00:33:05,000
You may have as many
people there as you need

609
00:33:05,000 --> 00:33:07,041
to guarantee her safety.

610
00:33:07,041 --> 00:33:11,125
But give us this chance
to vindicate ourselves.

611
00:33:14,333 --> 00:33:17,500
I will discuss the matter
with Counselor Troi.

612
00:33:24,709 --> 00:33:26,750
Well, that's it
for Melina II.

613
00:33:26,750 --> 00:33:28,458
No unexplained comas
during the time

614
00:33:28,458 --> 00:33:31,166
the Ullians
were working there.

615
00:33:31,166 --> 00:33:32,667
We have yet to
receive transmission

616
00:33:32,667 --> 00:33:34,542
from the two planets
of the Nel system.

617
00:33:34,542 --> 00:33:36,458
Perhaps they will
show different results.

618
00:33:36,458 --> 00:33:38,625
Maybe...

619
00:33:38,625 --> 00:33:42,792
and maybe we're not checking
for the right thing.

620
00:33:42,792 --> 00:33:44,417
Please clarify.

621
00:33:44,417 --> 00:33:47,542
We haven't looked into the
comas that<i> were</i> explained.

622
00:33:48,834 --> 00:33:50,166
Why would we do that?

623
00:33:50,166 --> 00:33:52,500
Well, remember what
Dr. Crusher said

624
00:33:52,500 --> 00:33:54,417
right after Counselor Troi
became unconscious--

625
00:33:54,417 --> 00:33:56,709
that it looked exactly
like Iresine Syndrome,

626
00:33:56,709 --> 00:33:58,291
except for the
histamine count?

627
00:33:58,291 --> 00:33:59,542
Yes.

628
00:33:59,542 --> 00:34:01,583
Well, maybe not
every medical facility

629
00:34:01,583 --> 00:34:03,458
is as careful as Dr. Crusher.

630
00:34:03,458 --> 00:34:06,375
Maybe it's easier to
just make a quick diagnosis

631
00:34:06,375 --> 00:34:09,500
rather than keep hunting
for the real cause.

632
00:34:09,500 --> 00:34:12,291
You are searching for instances
of Iresine Syndrome.

633
00:34:12,291 --> 00:34:14,458
Right...
And correlating them

634
00:34:14,458 --> 00:34:17,041
with the visits by
the Ullians and...

635
00:34:18,333 --> 00:34:19,625
And there we are.

636
00:34:19,625 --> 00:34:20,834
Two cases of
Iresine Syndrome

637
00:34:20,834 --> 00:34:22,417
on Hurada III,

638
00:34:22,417 --> 00:34:26,041
at exactly the time Tarmin
and his group were there.

639
00:34:26,041 --> 00:34:27,458
Let's check
the other planets.

640
00:34:27,458 --> 00:34:29,458
I think we may have
something here.

641
00:34:31,000 --> 00:34:32,542
Counselor,
I want to reiterate.

642
00:34:32,542 --> 00:34:34,375
If you have any
doubts whatsoever

643
00:34:34,375 --> 00:34:37,458
about this procedure, you don't
have to go through with it.

644
00:34:37,458 --> 00:34:39,834
I want to do it, Captain.

645
00:34:39,834 --> 00:34:41,417
Something awful
happened to me,

646
00:34:41,417 --> 00:34:43,750
and I don't even
know what it was.

647
00:34:45,458 --> 00:34:47,041
Very well.

648
00:34:48,875 --> 00:34:50,917
Counselor, what's the
last thing you remember

649
00:34:50,917 --> 00:34:53,458
about the other night?

650
00:34:53,458 --> 00:34:54,709
Brushing my hair.

651
00:34:54,709 --> 00:34:56,750
Would you get
your hairbrush?

652
00:35:05,083 --> 00:35:06,667
Tell me about
brushing your hair.

653
00:35:06,667 --> 00:35:08,208
Do you do it
every night?

654
00:35:08,208 --> 00:35:10,250
Yes, when I'm ready
for bed.

655
00:35:16,959 --> 00:35:18,417
What is it?

656
00:35:23,041 --> 00:35:24,792
Someone's touching my hair.

657
00:35:24,792 --> 00:35:27,333
Someone's with you
in the room?

658
00:35:28,709 --> 00:35:30,875
No.

659
00:35:30,875 --> 00:35:34,375
No, I'm alone.
There's no one there.

660
00:35:34,375 --> 00:35:36,125
Go on.

661
00:35:38,542 --> 00:35:41,083
I get some hot chocolate.

662
00:35:42,542 --> 00:35:45,291
Something's happening.

663
00:35:45,291 --> 00:35:48,125
I'm alone in my quarters.

664
00:35:48,125 --> 00:35:51,417
I'm remembering something
from a few years ago.

665
00:35:52,375 --> 00:35:53,917
Go back into
that memory.

666
00:35:53,917 --> 00:35:57,041
You said... someone
was touching your hair?

667
00:35:58,792 --> 00:36:02,000
Yes... and...

668
00:36:06,125 --> 00:36:08,166
it's Will Riker.

669
00:36:08,166 --> 00:36:10,291
That's right.
I was thinking of him.

670
00:36:10,291 --> 00:36:14,000
Remembering a time when
you were with him.

671
00:36:14,000 --> 00:36:16,834
Yes, after a poker game.

672
00:36:16,834 --> 00:36:19,291
It's a pleasant memory.
Stay with it.

673
00:36:23,291 --> 00:36:25,041
(<i> gasping</i> )

674
00:36:26,375 --> 00:36:28,625
Now, he's hurting me.

675
00:36:29,834 --> 00:36:32,792
You're... you're frightened.

676
00:36:32,792 --> 00:36:34,542
I want him to stop.

677
00:36:34,542 --> 00:36:36,542
(<i> sobbing</i> )

678
00:36:40,667 --> 00:36:42,583
(<i> gasps</i> )

679
00:36:42,583 --> 00:36:45,000
It's not Will.

680
00:36:45,000 --> 00:36:46,583
Somebody's taken
his place.

681
00:36:46,583 --> 00:36:48,125
Someone else is there,
who is it?

682
00:36:48,125 --> 00:36:50,709
(<i> crying</i> )
No...

683
00:36:50,709 --> 00:36:52,709
he shouldn't be here.

684
00:36:52,709 --> 00:36:54,291
Why is he here?

685
00:36:55,542 --> 00:36:57,208
Stop.
You're hurting me.

686
00:36:57,208 --> 00:36:59,417
Can you see his face?

687
00:36:59,417 --> 00:37:00,542
Yes.

688
00:37:00,542 --> 00:37:02,834
(<i> sobbing</i> )

689
00:37:05,125 --> 00:37:06,750
<i>Imzadi...</i>

690
00:37:06,750 --> 00:37:08,375
No! Stop!

691
00:37:08,375 --> 00:37:10,291
You're hurting me!

692
00:37:10,291 --> 00:37:12,375
Who is it?

693
00:37:12,375 --> 00:37:14,125
Who is doing this to you?

694
00:37:14,125 --> 00:37:16,125
(<i> gasps</i> )

695
00:37:20,375 --> 00:37:21,834
It's Tarmin.

696
00:37:23,709 --> 00:37:25,417
It's your father.

697
00:37:44,291 --> 00:37:47,834
<i>Captain's Log,</i>
<i>Stardate 45433.2.</i>

698
00:37:47,834 --> 00:37:49,959
<i>We have set a course</i>
<i>for Starbase 440</i>

699
00:37:49,959 --> 00:37:52,333
<i>where the Ullians</i>
<i>will disembark</i>

700
00:37:52,333 --> 00:37:53,917
<i>and return home.</i>

701
00:37:53,917 --> 00:37:56,667
Inad and I have contacted
our home planet.

702
00:37:56,667 --> 00:37:58,583
If you want to
prosecute my father,

703
00:37:58,583 --> 00:38:01,500
the authorities there
will support you.

704
00:38:01,500 --> 00:38:06,834
I'm not sure we have any legal
basis for such a prosecution.

705
00:38:06,834 --> 00:38:10,291
Memory invasion
is simply not a crime

706
00:38:10,291 --> 00:38:12,125
that we've ever had
to contend with.

707
00:38:12,125 --> 00:38:15,208
According to what I've
just learned, it's a practice

708
00:38:15,208 --> 00:38:18,458
that was abolished on our world
centuries ago.

709
00:38:18,458 --> 00:38:21,125
What could motivate
someone like your father

710
00:38:21,125 --> 00:38:23,375
to commit such an act?

711
00:38:23,375 --> 00:38:25,417
I don't know.

712
00:38:25,417 --> 00:38:28,750
A perverse source
of pleasure, perhaps.

713
00:38:28,750 --> 00:38:31,792
A way to exercise control
over another.

714
00:38:34,208 --> 00:38:35,792
Your father claims,

715
00:38:35,792 --> 00:38:38,250
quite strenuously,
that he's innocent.

716
00:38:38,250 --> 00:38:40,875
(<i> chuckles</i> )
My father has never been one

717
00:38:40,875 --> 00:38:43,333
to admit that he's wrong.

718
00:38:43,333 --> 00:38:46,750
But it is difficult to believe
he'd be capable of this.

719
00:38:48,417 --> 00:38:53,875
I am told that the punishment
for this crime is quite severe.

720
00:39:01,333 --> 00:39:04,959
We are monitoring my father's
telepathic activities.

721
00:39:04,959 --> 00:39:06,291
You have my assurance

722
00:39:06,291 --> 00:39:09,083
he won't assault
anyone else.

723
00:39:10,583 --> 00:39:13,625
I am sorry for this, Captain.

724
00:39:20,792 --> 00:39:22,667
Picard to Commander Data.

725
00:39:22,667 --> 00:39:23,875
DATA: Yes, Captain?

726
00:39:23,875 --> 00:39:25,166
How's your search coming?

727
00:39:25,166 --> 00:39:27,041
We have uncovered
several cases, sir,

728
00:39:27,041 --> 00:39:29,542
but have not yet completed
our investigation.

729
00:39:29,542 --> 00:39:31,917
We'll inform the medical
personnel on those planets

730
00:39:31,917 --> 00:39:35,166
that we have discovered the
true nature of the comas.

731
00:39:35,166 --> 00:39:37,959
I'm sure they'll appreciate
knowing what really happened.

732
00:39:37,959 --> 00:39:41,000
Yes, sir. We will
keep searching, sir.

733
00:39:41,000 --> 00:39:44,125
We just got the transmission
from the Nel system, Data.

734
00:39:44,125 --> 00:39:45,917
No mention of
Iresine Syndrome,

735
00:39:45,917 --> 00:39:47,667
but there are two
unexplained comas

736
00:39:47,667 --> 00:39:49,625
on one planet,
none on the other.

737
00:39:49,625 --> 00:39:51,625
And were the
Ullians present?

738
00:39:51,625 --> 00:39:54,166
Checking the mission logs.

739
00:39:55,917 --> 00:39:57,375
That's funny.

740
00:39:57,375 --> 00:40:01,917
On stardates
45321 and 45323,

741
00:40:01,917 --> 00:40:03,583
when the comas occurred,

742
00:40:03,583 --> 00:40:05,667
Tarmin was on
his home planet.

743
00:40:05,667 --> 00:40:08,375
He wasn't anywhere
near the Nel system.

744
00:40:09,959 --> 00:40:11,125
(<i> door chimes</i> )

745
00:40:11,125 --> 00:40:12,875
Come in.

746
00:40:16,417 --> 00:40:18,000
Hello, Jev.

747
00:40:18,000 --> 00:40:19,625
We'll be reaching
starbase soon.

748
00:40:19,625 --> 00:40:22,166
I wanted to say good-bye

749
00:40:22,166 --> 00:40:24,333
and to apologize
again for my father.

750
00:40:24,333 --> 00:40:25,917
There's no need.

751
00:40:25,917 --> 00:40:28,583
You're not responsible
for what he did.

752
00:40:28,583 --> 00:40:30,959
Before all this
happened, I...

753
00:40:30,959 --> 00:40:33,166
I had hoped we
might become friends.

754
00:40:33,166 --> 00:40:34,917
We still can.

755
00:40:34,917 --> 00:40:37,375
After what he's
put you through?

756
00:40:37,375 --> 00:40:40,083
Maybe you can forget.

757
00:40:40,083 --> 00:40:42,000
I'm not sure I can.

758
00:40:49,000 --> 00:40:51,625
You're so lovely.

759
00:40:52,750 --> 00:40:54,000
I have to go.

760
00:40:54,000 --> 00:40:55,750
Good-bye.

761
00:40:55,750 --> 00:40:58,875
Jev... you're upset.

762
00:40:58,875 --> 00:41:01,750
Would you like to talk?

763
00:41:01,750 --> 00:41:03,166
No.

764
00:41:03,166 --> 00:41:05,333
You'd feel better
if you did.

765
00:41:11,125 --> 00:41:13,208
Why do you have
to be so nice?

766
00:41:15,291 --> 00:41:18,917
So... so lovely.

767
00:41:28,959 --> 00:41:31,917
What... what's happening?

768
00:41:39,625 --> 00:41:41,250
It's happening again.

769
00:41:43,333 --> 00:41:46,000
You're so beautiful...

770
00:41:46,000 --> 00:41:47,583
so fragile.

771
00:41:49,166 --> 00:41:51,583
It was you.

772
00:41:51,583 --> 00:41:55,083
It was always you.

773
00:41:55,083 --> 00:41:57,166
Have you stopped
thinking about us?

774
00:41:57,166 --> 00:42:00,125
No!

775
00:42:00,125 --> 00:42:02,583
(<i> whimpering</i> )

776
00:42:02,583 --> 00:42:04,709
No..

777
00:42:06,125 --> 00:42:08,083
No! No!

778
00:42:08,083 --> 00:42:10,125
Don't! Don't!

779
00:42:10,125 --> 00:42:11,917
I won't let you.

780
00:42:18,250 --> 00:42:19,375
No!

781
00:42:19,375 --> 00:42:20,917
(<i> screams</i> )

782
00:42:24,625 --> 00:42:27,625
DATA:
Counselor...

783
00:42:27,625 --> 00:42:28,875
are you all right?

784
00:42:28,875 --> 00:42:30,709
Yes.

785
00:42:38,667 --> 00:42:41,542
Why are you here?
How did you know?

786
00:42:41,542 --> 00:42:44,250
We discovered two instances
of unexplained coma

787
00:42:44,250 --> 00:42:46,458
on Nel Three while
the Ullians were there,

788
00:42:46,458 --> 00:42:48,208
but Tarmin was not
part of the group.

789
00:42:48,208 --> 00:42:49,875
Further examination
revealed

790
00:42:49,875 --> 00:42:51,417
that there was only
one Ullian present

791
00:42:51,417 --> 00:42:55,208
for all incidents
of coma-- Jev.

792
00:43:00,250 --> 00:43:03,834
<i>Captain's Log,</i>
<i>Stardate 45435.8.</i>

793
00:43:03,834 --> 00:43:06,959
<i>Dr. Crusher and Commander Riker</i>
<i>regained consciousness</i>

794
00:43:06,959 --> 00:43:09,333
<i>while we were en route</i>
<i>to the Ullian home world.</i>

795
00:43:09,333 --> 00:43:12,667
<i>The slow process</i>
<i>of their recovery has begun.</i>

796
00:43:12,667 --> 00:43:15,583
I have asked that the finest
physicians on my world

797
00:43:15,583 --> 00:43:18,834
meet with you all
upon our return, to help you

798
00:43:18,834 --> 00:43:20,458
in your healing process.

799
00:43:20,458 --> 00:43:22,667
They've been in contact
with us already.

800
00:43:22,667 --> 00:43:23,917
Thank you.

801
00:43:23,917 --> 00:43:25,583
It's been three centuries

802
00:43:25,583 --> 00:43:29,291
since we treated
anyone for this...

803
00:43:29,291 --> 00:43:30,792
this form of rape.

804
00:43:30,792 --> 00:43:34,208
But there are medical
records from that era.

805
00:43:34,208 --> 00:43:37,792
It was a time of great
violence for my people--

806
00:43:37,792 --> 00:43:40,959
a time we thought we had
put far behind us.

807
00:43:42,583 --> 00:43:45,959
That this could happen now...

808
00:43:45,959 --> 00:43:47,500
is unimaginable.

809
00:43:47,500 --> 00:43:50,709
Earth was once
a violent planet too.

810
00:43:50,709 --> 00:43:53,709
At times, the chaos threatened
the very fabric of life.

811
00:43:53,709 --> 00:43:56,208
But like you, we evolved.

812
00:43:56,208 --> 00:44:00,250
We found better ways to
handle our conflicts.

813
00:44:00,250 --> 00:44:02,500
But I think no one can deny

814
00:44:02,500 --> 00:44:08,375
that the seed of violence
remains within each of us.

815
00:44:09,792 --> 00:44:14,291
We must recognize that,
because that violence

816
00:44:14,291 --> 00:44:18,041
is capable of
consuming each of us,

817
00:44:18,041 --> 00:44:20,250
as it consumed your son.
